$interpreted: Hestia: How many times have you come here!? So sick of this! Do I have to tell you again? This isn't your territory!
Karnulla: Blah blah blah! Recently, humans have been wandering about in our space. You lowlifes, how could you know how tough it is for us!?
Hestia: Humans? Another poacher? I haven't seen any.
Hestia: This ain't right. Your words mean nothing to me. I want to talk with Yan-Bo about this...
Karnulla: You think that stinky old fart is still the boss of me? He had nothing on me a long time ago, you dirty fish!
Karnulla: I'm gonna gobble you all up in a hot minute!
Law: ...Young lad, restrain yourself.
Hestia: Law...?
Karnulla: Who are you, old fart? So we've got ourselves a poet, eh?
Law: I once knew a young fellow who sought revenge for his master, massacring the entire tribe of his enemy. His hands were bathed in blood.
Law: Me lad, I advise thee to not follow in his footsteps.
Karnulla: What and what? He's got nothing to do with me!
Law: This I don't deny...that young lad's enemy took the wrong road and made mistakes due to his selfish desire.
Law: But I doth believe, he did not intend to slay the master, and to this very day, even when he is drunk as can be, he still can't forget that fateful day.
Hestia: Drunk...?
Law: Head back; today I shall protect Hestia.
Karnulla: You talk a big talk, but the point is, you're on her side! Since that's the case, can't blame me. Let's get 'em boys!
Law: One.
Law: Two. This is your final warning. Thou best return hastily.
Karnulla: Enough with the crappy act!
Karnulla: Hehe, taste my fangs...
Law: ...Three.
Law: Twas thine own doing, now face the fires of fate!
Karnulla: *cough*...*cough*...damn! This dog is almost as strong as Yan-Bo...
Karnulla: ...Damn, can't move...
Law: Where did thee bluster and bravado go to? I warned thee, and yet ye insist on thy unruly ways!
Hestia: No...please stop, Law! We're safe, let him go!
Law: This has naught to do with thee!
Law: I shalt not allow thee to become like that young lad, a lowly sinner, inflicting suffering on the weak and needy!
Law: Today I shalt carry out justice for the heavens and have thee removed from this earth!
Karnulla: Don't, don't come any closer! Don't──
Law: What are ye doing...Yan-Bo!
Karnulla: Y-You old brute, what the...
Yan-Bo: Karnulla, leave. Now...
Yan-Bo: Old friend, restrain yourself. Deserve this, he does not.
Law: Be gone! Ye hast not the authority to stop me!
Law: Fleeing all these years, ye must be 'ware, 'twas I who've borne the shambles thee left behind!
Yan-Bo: The authority to request such a favor, I have not. But spare his life, I ask of you.
Yan-Bo: Let down this child again, I will not.
Yan-Bo: ...Flee from troubles again, I shall no longer.
Law: ...To hear these words, I have waited ages.
Law: Good, very good.
Law: Excellent!
Law: I trust ye words.
Law: ──Frog, now SCRAM!
Law: Glorious wine.
Yan-Bo: The fermentation, no matter how it's done...produce the taste we had in olden days, I cannot.
Law: A jester's words! The taste of new wine is exquisite, what need is there to think of days past? Don't hold onto that old bottle, 'twill only turn bad.
Law: ...No matter what the masses said of thee then, both Maeok and I believe ye.
Law: But ye never gave me a chance, to tell thee. Ye left without word, leaving me to find ye.
Law: ...Afterwards, for ye, Maeok even...
Law: ...No, I've spoken too much.
Law: That is in the past.
Yan-Bo: Law, may I ask...Maeok, is she well?
Law: The same. Ye know well, the burden of the alliance is as it is...no need to worry for her.
Yan-Bo: Indeed...hehe...
